			CAS-DTM-MY38_034521_354_1-OPD-03-01.asc
	  
				The DTM is a GEOTiff file (extension: Tiff, IMG (for future PDS4) or CDF (new format)) 
				defined by a matrix which maximum size has to be 2048x8400 of double/float.	  
				
				The DTM file name includes:
				- Characters indicating that the file is a CaSSIS DTM: CAS-DTM
				- Stereo pair image IDs
				- Three letters that indicate which institution produced the DTM (e.g. _USG_
				for USGS, _OAP_ for OAPD, _UOA_ for Univ. of Arizona, etc.)
				- A grid spacing code (two-digit integer) 04 means 4.6 meters
				- A version number (2 digits) (e.g. 01, 02, etc.)
				
				DTM are generated throwgh 3DPD pipeline[*]
				Pipeline includes:
					-SURF tie points
					-Delaunay Triangulation
					-NCC pyramidal 3 level disparity definition
					-Parabolic subpixel refinement   
					-LSM [12x12] affine based subpixel refinement   
				Height are defined on MOLA datum:
				https://pds-geosciences.wustl.edu/missions/mgs/megdr.html
				MOLA VERSION:megR_hb
				R = radius
				h = 128 pix / deg
				version = b
			
  
			CAS-HMP-MY38_034521_354_1-OPD-03-01.jpg
			
				It represents the Texturized RGB height map of the DTM.	  
	  
			CAS-QMP-MY38_034521_354_1-OPD-03-01.jpg
			
				It represents the Figure of Merit of the DTM.
				It associates to each pixel the fidelity of the DTM height.
				Low correlation (BLACK to YELLOW): all the pixel with Affine NCC<0.5
				Medium correlation (YELLOW to BLUE): all the pixel with Affine 0.5<NCC<0.7
				High correlation  (BLU to GREEN): all the pixel with Affine NCC>0.7
				Interpolate (RED): Deformable models

			CAS-OTH-MY38_034521_354_1-OPD-03-01-PAN_1.asc
				Full resolution orthoimage of the master image.
						
	
